In shutdown, sys.exit() is called before self.engine_core_sentinel.shutdown(), making the sentinel shutdown code completely unreachable. We should shut down the sentinel first before exiting the process.
The return value of self._execute_command_on_workers is ignored in retry. If the workers fail to recover or time out, the retry operation will still return success=True, leading to silent failures and inconsistent cluster states. We should capture and return the result of the worker command execution.
